A new file is a file you created inside your project folder, but Git is not tracking it yet.

Git can see the file, but Git is not watching it yet.


We create new files because projects need files like:

    index.html

    style.css
    
    script.js
    
    README.md

But after creating a file, we need to check if Git knows about it.

That is why we use:

  git status

git status tells you what is happening in your Git project.

